reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute caddy for small lightweight items !
reviews.reviewText: This is a very cute lightweight caddy you can attach to the side of baby’s crib or bassinet. The material is a soft lightweight material so it will sag if you put items that are too heavy for example, a glass baby bottle. I have found this caddy to hold perfectly a few bibs, or burp cloths, and a stuffed animal, paci or teether.

reviews.reviewText: so i wanted something to have on my crib on, to have an wuick access to cleaning essentials and toysfirst thing i noticed is minor stitching defects, specially the double folded cord stitching on the sidethe pocket size is big enough to added various things... but when i added a baby lotion which have corners resembling like a toothpaste tube, made a small tear...so the quality is not that great as it appears, considering the small tear by a small itemmy suggestion to everyone is to add simple little things like small toys or towel/pampers... nothing heavy or pointy.my kid does enjoy pulling on these cords but it is not that heavy duty, again concern about durability. i really hope it don't break!here is a suggestion for seller: it would be helpful to add a second layer sleeve inside the pocket, specially for durability and perhaps a bit heavy duty cord for those who like to pull these.overall the color and style is nice

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I *love* this little caddy, perfect bedside storage (for kids or adults!)
reviews.reviewText: I got this because I don't have a nightstand or dresser anymore (house got trashed by flooding from a hurricane, have had to re-do everything & just can't afford to replace *all* the furniture), and I have a lot of stuff that I use in/near the bed - my kindle especially, but also ear plugs, chapstick, books, Flonase, phone sometimes, etc. And this lined up perfectly with the slats of the bedframe to tie it in place, and it's inconspicuous and really cute. I really like that it's fabric, so it's totally washable if it ever gets dusty/dirty. And it really holds a decent amount of stuff, I have all those things in there and there's still plenty of extra space left. Now, even in the dark, I can reach into the pocket & grab my ear plugs or kindle without having to turn on the light, bump around making noise, etc. & wake everyone else up. So, it's really helpful for me, & now I don't just have junk piled up on the windowsill next to the bed anymore. I love it.And this would also work great for a crib or a kid's bed, too, I would think. I checked & it also lines up with the slats on my daughter's bed, so it would tie onto there fine too.Definitely 5 stars on this one.
